Follow the dream. That’s all. ✨

#Positivity #PositiveMindset #ChaseYourDream #Growth #GrowthMindset

This is me. I spent YEARS avoiding the stage. I didn’t feel worthy enough to share my passion. I constantly told myself I wasn’t good enough. I was either upset because my voice was too “low” or I didn’t have that powerhouse sound. Long story short, my anxiety and imposter syndrome led me to self-sabotage…A LOT. To give you an idea, I began singing when I was 6 years old. I didn’t touch a stage until 10 years later. 

Personally, I still see the perfectionist in this video. This was about a year ago for those wondering. She’s still a bit nervous and learning her way. She is working on her stage presence and feeling comfortable. She’s starting to realize the world isn’t against her. 

I find it important to talk about these things because you never know if someone else is feeling the exact same. If you happen to know someone that is scared to chase their passion, please send them this. Let them know they’re not alone. I am not voicing this for just artists. I am voicing this for all those that have a dream.

To those person that got sent this - you CAN do it. I’m not going to tell you your mind will always be nice to you. We all have bad days no matter what. However, those 3.5 minutes of courage I found within myself to step on stage changed my life forever. You’ll always wonder “what if?” otherwise. Whatever sets your soul on fire is your true purpose in life. Don’t let anyone tell you different 🤍 

If you want to know my full story, i’m happy to make a video about it. I just wanted to give a quick shoutout to those experiencing the same as I did. I hope this helps 🤍

P.S. I’m still not perfect and no one is - we’re human. However, I’m chasing this dream regardless. You owe it to yourself to do the same. Sometimes it just takes a few minutes of courage to jump start everything you’ve always wanted to do…

Thank you for showing up this year. I never thought I’d experience the feeling of having others connect with my music. Now, I can confidently say that it’s the greatest gift of all. Merry Christmas to you and your family. Never lose sight of the dreams you’ve always had 🎄✨❤️

“I GREW UP BELIEVING I WASN’T GOOD ENOUGH. I SPENT MANY NIGHTS CRYING ON MY FLOOR WONDERING IF I WOULD EVER GET OUT OF MY
OWN HEAD. MUSIC WAS MY BEST FRIEND BEFORE ANYONE EVEN KNEW I COULD SING. IT GAVE ME A PURPOSE WHEN I COULDN’T FIND ONE WITHIN MYSELF. 

FAST FORWARD TO NOW -  I RECORDED 3 ORIGINAL SINGLES AND DID MY
FIRST EVER MUSIC VIDEOS. MY LATEST SINGLE HAS 10K+ STREAMS. I LEFT MY HOMETOWN  RECENTLY AND I MOVED TO NASHVILLE. SO MANY OF YOU SHOWED UP FOR ME WHEN YOU DIDN’T HAVE TO. ALL I’VE EVER WANTED WAS FOR PEOPLE TO CONNECT WITH MY MUSIC. I WANTED IT TO HELP THEM THE SAME WAY IT ALWAYS HAS FOR
ME. 

THANK YOU FOR GIVING ME THAT GIFT THIS YEAR. I AM ETERNALLY GRATEFUL. 

NEVER GIVE UP ON YOURSELF BECAUSE YOU DON’T FEEL GOOD ENOUGH/ARE AFRAID OF FAILURE. YOU’LL NEVER KNOW OTHERWISE. 🤍” 

*No I did not know this would copy and paste in all caps😂*
